Functional for very basic situations but runs into issues with anything complex enough to be worthy of Tasker integration.  Really needs the ability to test connection status and provide other information to Tasker.  Until this is updated, save your money.

This is barely functional and the functionality hasn't been fixed. The software needs to detect the status of the actions it carries out and should be updated to pass back information for Tasker to act on. The developers have refused to respond to requests for this functionality.  Usage Scenario that this is a pain for: You need to trigger three port forwards (because JuiceSSH can't do ranges). If you set up a task using this three times, it tries to start three instances of JuiceSSH (which isn't allowed), and you end up with only the first tunnel connecting. There's no way to set up a pause other than a hard-coded "wait" of X seconds, which makes running the tasks impractical. I may as well just fire all three one at a time manually.  This needs some TLC from the developers based on feedback from paying customers. Bought it in hopes that more development was coming, but it seems that this wasn't true.

Trying to toggle more that 1 port forward doesn't work. Only the 1st one turns on or off. It would work if this plugin waited until the 1st forward finished before it tried to start the next one. The work around is to put a 5-8 second delay in your script between each port forward. Hopefully this will be fixed in the future.
